Hull City have completed the signing of Lokomotiv Moscow striker Dame N'Doye for £3million.

The 29-year-old joins the Tigers on a two-and-a-half year deal with the option for a third. 

Steve Bruce had been in Paris for the majority of transfer deadline day trying to push the deal through before the closure of the window.

